<TITLE> US envoy for women's issues due Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 9 (bdnews24.com)  Melanne Verveer, the US ambassador-at-large for global women's issues, will visit Bangladesh from Tuesday. Ambassador Verveer during the three-day visit will meet with government officials, politicians, and business and civil society leaders to discuss a range of bilateral and multilateral issues, with special focus on women's development. In her capacity as director of the US State Department's new office on Global Women's Issues, she coordinates foreign policy issues and activities relating to the political, economic and social advancement of women around the world. Appointed by President Barack Obama, Verveer is the first ambassador-at-large for global women's issues, a US embassy press release says. The president's decision to create the position is unprecedented, and reflects the elevated importance of these issues to the Obama administration, says the embassy. Verveer served as chief of staff for then First Lady Hillary Clinton and visited Bangladesh with her in 1995
